verses.roman:
aṅganete dūre rahi' karena praṇipāta
mukunda-datta kahe,--'ei āila raghunātha'

synonyms: aṅganete—in the courtyard; dūre rahi'-keeping himself at a distant place; karena praṇipāta—offered his obeisances; mukunda-datta kahe—Mukunda Datta said; ei—this; āila—has come; raghunātha—Raghunātha dāsa.
translation: Staying at a distant place in the courtyard, he fell down to offer obeisances. Then Mukunda Datta said, "Here is Raghunātha."
